04/09/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Seven workers were killed and 14 were injured late Thursday (September 3rd) in a series of explosions at the Prvi Partizan ammunition factory in the town of Uzice. 
Interior Minister Ivica Dacic visited the scene and said an investigation into the explosion and fire that then erupted is under way. 
Prvi Partizan is Serbia's largest ammunition factory, producing military and hunting ammunition as well as gun powder and explosives. 
Uzice will observe a three-day mourning period. 
(Beta, RTS, B92, Tanjug, AP, Reuters - 04/09/09)
